The paper deals with nonlinear precoders for multiuser massive MIMO systems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI) communities. The paper also considers hardware limitations, such as restricted number of active antennas, which falls under the networked and distributed systems (cs.NI) category. The large-system performance analysis using the replica method is a common technique in statistical physics (cs.SP) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. Therefore, these five categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
